basics.headline: Full Stack Engineer, with a focus on backend development.
basics.summary: Developing powerful and dynamic applications, using some of the latest technologies, that are stable, reliable and productive.

work.summary: As a Software Engineer at Northwestern Mutual, I have been actively engaged in Java-based projects, focusing primarily on Backend/Services development. Leveraging my expertise, I've contributed to the successful implementation of solutions utilizing Java frameworks like Spring, Drools, and Flowable. Over the past 2 years and 4 months, I have continuously honed my skills in these technologies and remained enthusiastic about exploring innovative applications to deliver exceptional results.
highlights: Proficient in Java development with a focus on Backend/Services engineering.
Extensive experience working with Spring, Drools, and Flowable frameworks.
Consistently seeking opportunities to enhance my skillset and stay up-to-date with the latest technologies
Proven track record of delivering high-quality solutions in a dynamic work environment.

work.summary: As a Senior Software Engineer at Brady Corporation, I played a crucial role in the development of their e-commerce platform. Serving as a full-stack developer, I adeptly utilized a diverse set of tools and technologies, including SASS Stylesheets, JavaScript, and various JavaScript frameworks. Employing the principles of MVC (Model-View-Controller) and Test Driven Development (TDD), I contributed to the creation of robust and efficient solutions. Additionally, I gained valuable experience in Docker containerization, which led to the successful implementation of one-click 'Dev environments as code' setup scripts. These scripts significantly streamlined the onboarding process and machine rebuilding, positively impacting the team's productivity. Throughout my 9-month tenure at Brady, I remained dedicated to optimizing the development process and enhancing the overall efficiency of our team.
highlights: Proficient in full-stack development, focusing on the e-commerce domain.
Skilled in utilizing SASS Stylesheets, JavaScript, and various JavaScript frameworks.
Demonstrated expertise in applying MVC and Test Driven Development methodologies.
Experience with Docker containerization, leading to efficient one-click 'Dev environments as code' setup.
Strong commitment to process optimization and team productivity improvements.

work.position: App Software Analyst (Mid to Senior Software Engineer)
work.summary: As a Software Engineer (Application Software Analyst) at Trisept Solutions, I served as a Software Engineer with a variety of functions, driving backend system development, mentoring team members, and providing valuable insights on system performance. Previously, I excelled as the lead developer for the break-fix team, resolving issues across the entire system. Actively involved in sub-committees, I focused on enhancing company morale and wellness initiatives. I represented Trisept as a speaker at 'COSBE be the spark,' showcasing custom AI-powered applications. Additionally, I collaborated with Microsoft, gaining expertise in Azure deployment, bot technologies, and cognitive services through a hands-on hackathon. My passion for innovation and process improvement contributed to the success of our team.
highlights: Demonstrated leadership as the Development Lead for the Product Support area, driving backend system development.
Proficient in full-stack development, utilizing a diverse range of tools and technologies.
Proven ability in providing setup materials/documentation and offering valuable insights on system performance and monitoring.
Effective mentorship of new and junior developers, fostering growth and skill development within the team.
Actively involved in sub-committees, contributing to company morale and wellness initiatives.
Engaged in public speaking, representing Trisept and showcasing innovative applications at 'COSBE be the spark.'
Collaborated with Microsoft, focusing on Azure deployment, bot technologies, and cognitive services, culminating in a custom chatbot development.

work.summary: As a Software Engineer at Blue7 Solutions, I held dual roles, serving as a Consultant Development Lead for the Product Support team and a full-stack developer for Trisept Solutions' dynamic packaging engine. In my capacity as a Consultant Development Lead, I collaborated closely with Trisept Solutions and Blue7 Solutions' offshore resources, proficiently debugging and resolving code-related issues throughout Trisept's entire system. Beyond my technical contributions, I actively participated in Blue7 Solutions' wellness and event planning team, organizing events, engaging in community outreach, and promoting the company's initiatives. As a consultant, I effectively managed project hours and ensured adherence to hourly constraints. My experience at Blue7 Solutions was enriching, allowing me to cultivate diverse skills, from technical expertise to cross-functional collaboration and project management.
highlights: Held dual roles as a Consultant Development Lead for the Product Support team and a full-stack developer for Trisept Solutions' dynamic packaging engine.
Collaborated closely with Trisept Solutions and Blue7 Solutions' offshore resources to debug and resolve issues, demonstrating in-depth knowledge of Trisept's entire system.
Actively contributed to Blue7 Solutions' wellness and event planning team, organizing events, participating in community outreach, and promoting company initiatives.
Proficiently managed project hours and maintained project deliverables within hourly constraints.
Developed a diverse skill set, encompassing technical expertise, cross-functional collaboration, and project management.

work.summary: As a Software Developer at Trisept Solutions from May 2006 to Dec 2011, I played a vital role in developing and maintaining the dynamic packaging and booking engines. Utilizing technologies like C#, VB.net, SQL, XML, JavaScript, and ASP.net, I contributed to the development of 'Solutions by Trisept' web interface and WCF services on the .NET framework. Additionally, I led the migration from the 2.0 to 4.0 .NET framework and upgraded solutions to Visual Studio 2010. I collaborated with offshore teams, developed Windows Services, and ensured code adherence to industry security standards, including OWASP Top 10 certification for PCI compliance. My experience equipped me with a profound understanding of software development lifecycles and strong collaboration skills, contributing to the success of development projects.
highlights: Contributed significantly to the development and maintenance of Trisept Solutions' dynamic packaging and booking engines.
Proficiently utilized technologies such as C#, VB.net, SQL, XML, JavaScript, and ASP.net in software development.
Played a key role in the maintenance of 'Solutions by Trisept' web interface and the development of WCF services on the .NET framework.
Led the technical migration from the 2.0 to 4.0 .NET framework.
Collaborated effectively with offshore development teams to enhance project outcomes.
Developed one-off Windows Services to meet specific project requirements.
Ensured adherence to industry security standards, securing OWASP Top 10 certification for PCI compliance.
Demonstrated a comprehensive understanding of software development lifecycles.
Strong team player, contributing to the success of various development projects.

work.summary: As an Adjunct Instructor at ITT Technical Institute, I taught an overview course in the computing field and computer technology trends, with a focus on PC hardware and software components and their functions. Utilizing a hands-on approach, I facilitated both entry-level practical skills and theoretical understanding of PC hardware, presenting the course material concisely and encouraging students to apply their knowledge in real-world scenarios. I conducted interactive and detailed lessons, demonstrating hardware repair methods and troubleshooting techniques to provide students with practical experience in the subject matter.
highlights: Instructed an overview course in the computing field and computer technology trends.
Emphasized terminology and concepts related to PC hardware and software components.
Utilized a hands-on approach to teach entry-level skills and theory in PC hardware handling.
Encouraged students to apply theoretical knowledge to real-world settings.
Demonstrated hardware repair methods and troubleshooting through interactive lessons.
Administered and corrected examinations and homework assignments.
Provided academic support to students through office hours outside of normal work hours.
Successfully managed class sizes ranging from 20 to 30 students.
Developed strong instructional and presentation skills.
Acquired expertise in demonstrating hardware repair methods and troubleshooting techniques.

Encouraging practical application, I presented the material concisely to help students bridge theoretical concepts with real-world scenarios.

work.summary: As a Teaching Assistant at the University of Wisconsin Milwaukee, I supported the Web Application Development course (BusAdm 531) under Marc Haines. In this role, I graded papers and provided academic support to students, offering assistance with the course material and addressing any issues they encountered during the class. My guidance aimed to help students excel in the course, and this experience honed my communication skills and ability to provide valuable feedback.
highlights: Served as a Teaching Assistant for BusAdm 531 Web Application Development at the University of Wisconsin Milwaukee.
Responsible for grading papers and providing academic support to students.
Assisted students with course material and addressed any issues they faced during the class.
Offered guidance to help students succeed in the course.
Developed strong communication skills through interactions with students.
Gained proficiency in providing effective feedback to aid students' academic progress.
